In cantera@yahoogroups.com, "anders_hamstr" <anders.hammer.stromman@n.
..> wrote:
> I have been trying out this package over the last few days and have 
> really enjoyed it. I do however wonder if somone has compiled a 
> reference manual or user's guide specifically for the Matlab 
> interface. A quick reference guide e.g a list of 
> functions/methods/objects would also do the job.

I don't know of such a reference manual offhand (there may be one), 
but a simple way to get a list of objects is to look in the Cantera 
toolbox directory at the names of the directories that start with "@". 
 (There's also a Contents.m file in there which may be useful to look 
at.)  Then, you can get a list of methods for the objects either with 
Matlabs "methods" function, or by looking in the object directories.

- Brooks
